From: nix-wasm <eric@codebutler.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] virtio_wasm: register 8 single-port virtio-console devices

Register EIGHT single-port virtio-console devices on the wasm virtio
transport so the stock mainline virtio-console driver
(drivers/char/virtio_console.c, CONFIG_VIRTIO_CONSOLE) provides the
guest's consoles (hvc0..hvc7), replacing the retired bespoke hvc_wasm
backend (formerly patches 0002/0003, dropped in kernel.nix). This is the
console edition of the "everything is a virtio device" consolidation
(issue #10 / #83): the guest's TTYs ride the same virtio_wasm carrier the
9p / blk / net / vsock devices already use.

SINGLE PORT PER DEVICE (no VIRTIO_CONSOLE_F_MULTIPORT), EIGHT DEVICES.
A featureless virtio-console device gets exactly ONE port (port 0), which
mainline virtio_console wires to an hvc console line: vq[0]=receiveq
(host->guest input), vq[1]=transmitq (guest->host output). Critically,
the non-multiport probe path registers that hvc line SYNCHRONOUSLY during
device probe (add_port(0) -> init_port_console -> hvc_alloc), so the
console exists before PID 1 opens /dev/console.

Why not one MULTIPORT device with 8 ports? VIRTIO_CONSOLE_F_MULTIPORT
adds its ports ASYNCHRONOUSLY: probe only emits a control-vq
DEVICE_READY, and each port is added later when the host replies with a
PORT_ADD control message. On the single-CPU wasm boot the control-vq
handshake does not complete before init runs and dies ("Attempted to
kill init") -- hvc0 never registers in time. The pinned virtio_console.c
has no earlycon and does not wait on the port handshake. So the correct,
race-free way to get N consoles is N featureless devices, each taking the
synchronous single-port path. We therefore offer NO feature bits.

hvc line index == device registration order == host device index minus
VW_DEV_CONSOLE_BASE. The host serves each device via
runtime/virtio/console-device.js (CONSOLE_BASE = 8, CONSOLE_DEVICES = 8).

Device index: pinned to an explicit base (VW_DEV_CONSOLE_BASE = 8) so the
8 console host indices 8..15 stay stable regardless of which
CONFIG-guarded earlier slots are built, and so they never collide with
the vsock device (index 7, patch 0020). Index 6 is intentionally left
unused. Guarded by IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_VIRTIO_CONSOLE) so the enum slot and
the init loop are a no-op when the stock virtio-console driver is not
built.

VIRTIO_CONSOLE_F_SIZE (cols/rows in config space, the TIOCGWINSZ source)
is deliberately NOT offered yet: a single-port size change is delivered
via a virtio config-change interrupt, which the virtio_wasm transport
does not implement. Terminal resize is therefore a documented follow-up
(console_resize is a host-side no-op for now), not stubbed in the kernel.

The default 64-entry vq is fine: virtio_console moves a TTY byte stream
in small page-sized chunks (no 9p-style 128-page msize chain), so no
per-id qsize override is needed.

Part of issue #10 / #83 (host<->guest bridge consolidation onto virtio).
---
 drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c | 29 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 29 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c b/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
index d22cd22..7ec9114 100644
--- a/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
+++ b/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
@@ -377,6 +377,14 @@ enum {
 #if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_NET_9P_VIRTIO)
 	VW_DEV_9P_ROOT,		/* virtio-9p: pc VFS export (mount tag "pcroot") */
 	VW_DEV_9P_NIXCACHE,	/* virtio-9p: nix binary cache (tag "nixcache") */
+#endif
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_VIRTIO_CONSOLE)
+	/*
+	 * 8 single-port virtio-console lines (hvc0..hvc7) at host index 8..15.
+	 * Pinned with an explicit base so the host (CONSOLE_BASE = 8) and the
+	 * kernel agree on the index range; index 6 is intentionally unused.
+	 */
+	VW_DEV_CONSOLE_BASE = 8,
 #endif
 	VW_DEV_COUNT,
 };
@@ -423,6 +431,27 @@ static int __init virtio_wasm_transport_init(void)
 		pr_warn("virtio_wasm: 9p nixcache register failed: %ld\n", PTR_ERR(vw));
 #endif
 
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_VIRTIO_CONSOLE)
+	/*
+	 * 8 single-port virtio-console lines (stock drivers/char/virtio_console.c).
+	 * A featureless device gets exactly ONE port (port 0), which the driver
+	 * wires to an hvc console line SYNCHRONOUSLY during probe: vq[0]=receiveq
+	 * (host->guest input), vq[1]=transmitq (guest->host output). Registering
+	 * synchronously means the console line exists before PID 1 opens
+	 * /dev/console -- VIRTIO_CONSOLE_F_MULTIPORT would instead add ports
+	 * asynchronously via the control vq, which races init to death on a
+	 * single-CPU wasm boot. hvc line index == registration order == host
+	 * device index - VW_DEV_CONSOLE_BASE. The host serves each device via
+	 * runtime/virtio/console-device.js.
+	 */
+	for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
+		vw = virtio_wasm_register(VW_DEV_CONSOLE_BASE + i, VIRTIO_ID_CONSOLE);
+		if (IS_ERR(vw))
+			pr_warn("virtio_wasm: console %d register failed: %ld\n",
+				i, PTR_ERR(vw));
+	}
+#endif
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
--
2.53.0
